olive oil
1 packet fusilli
1 carrot
1 stalk celery
1 packet beef & pork mince
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet bechamel sauce
1 packet romesco sauce
20 g butter
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a large saucepan with boiling water, then add a
generous pinch of salt.
• Cook fusilli, uncovered, over high heat until ‘al dente’, 12 minutes.
• Reserve some pasta water (1/2 cup for 2 people / 1 cup for 4 people), drain
fusilli and return to saucepan.

• Meanwhile, grate carrot. Finely chop celery.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. Cook beef &
pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.

Little cooks: Under adult supervision, kids can help with grating the carrot.

• Add carrot and celery, stirring, until softened, 4-6 minutes.
• Add garlic & herb seasoning and Aussie spice blend, and cook until
fragrant, 1 minute.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add bechamel sauce, the butter and reserved
pasta water, and cook, stirring, until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, add romesco sauce, cooked fusilli and baby
spinach leaves and stir to combine. Season to taste.

• Divide creamy beef and pork romesco fusilli between bowls. Sprinkle over
grated Parmesan cheese to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling the cheese on top.